    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 25.416,
      "end": 26.877,
      "text": "The Wolf and the Lamb.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 30.52,
      "end": 39.062,
      "text": "A wolf came upon a lamb, straying from the flock, and felt some compunction about taking the life of so helpless a creature, without some plausible excuse.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 40.082,
      "end": 45.863,
      "text": "So he cast about four grievance and said at last, Last year, Sarah, you grossly insulted me.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 47.463,
      "end": 50.904,
      "text": "That is impossible, sir, pleaded the lamb, for I wasn't bored then.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 52.164,
      "end": 55.345,
      "text": "Well, retorted the wolf, you feed in my pastures.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 56.714,
      "end": 61.395,
      "text": "That cannot be,\" replied the lamb, for I have never yet tasted grass.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 62.976,
      "end": 65.937,
      "text": "You drink from my spring then, continued the wolf.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 66.897,
      "end": 72.059,
      "text": "Indeed, sir, said the poor lamb, I have never yet drunk anything but my mother's milk.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-014",
      "start": 73.239,
      "end": 80.661,
      "text": "Well, anyhow, said the wolf, I'm not going without my dinner, and he sprang upon the lamb and devoured it without more ado.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-015",
      "start": 83.742,
      "end": 85.623,
      "text": "End of the wolf and the lamb.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
